Those "my husband said he no longer loves me after giving birth to our child" or "I found my gf slept with 400 guys in college" stories are very pernicious because well-meaning but naive normal people get exposed to them and assume it's something that can actually happen to them.

The anonymous aspects of those stories makes them seem universal and random instead of unique cases of dysfunction, same way as the paranoia about AIDS among regular people in the recent past driven by TV news panic. The only way to stop anxiety in normies is white hat censorship

The societal role of intellectuals is to drag normies above their natural slop inclinations and elevate them to new heights spiritually, but with infinite slop content creation normies can now fester forever in those content swamps. Something needs to be done... Save the normies.

Was thinking about this post and how many dichotomies and debates are probably fundamentally reducible to choosing between English and French gardens. Admittedly I prefer the English style myself. All Slavs are anglophiles.

Even without knowing it or looking it up you can immediately tell that the French garden finds its origins in the monarchy of King Louis XIV, the Sun King, together with countless other things no one suspects.
